Question: Explain to a child how to do a task (e.g., cross the street).
Answer:
Sometimes there wont be anyone around to make you any food, so you should know how to make some for yourself. In order to make mac and cheese, put some water in a pot and turn on the burner at high temperature. Once the water boils, pour in the pasta from the box. This part will take 7-10 minutes depending on the pasta, so put a colinder in the sink for the next step. When the pasta is tender, pour the pot into the colinder. Then, put the pasta back in the pot, stir in the cheese, and you're done!